deck_excerpt: Zombies have come a long way
deck_description:
This deck was made with the June 8th banlist in mind.

It has been five months since I last made a zombies deck, and things have gotten out of control very quickly. Five months ago Deer Note wasn't even in Master Duel and Dante was in everyones ED to unbrick bad hands with Uni and E-Tele. Now? Zombies can mill a sixty card deck without grass, spam every lvl 8 and 10 synchro possible, they can scythe lock, have a floodgate field spell that can burden the best deck in the meta, and stops the second best deck, Floowandereeze, altogether. All this while no longer getting locked into zombies. Honestly this deck has become comparable to Adamancipators. Where Adamancipators still has less potential to brick an opening, the end board zombies can make deprecates on Adamacipators as a deck that utilizes a monster type rather than an archetype. You can do anything. Rarely have I not had all three mezuki in grave along with changshi, Chaos Ruler and Doomking. Put whatever you want in the Extra Deck, it doesn't matter, if it is generic and good (or not), zombies will make it. Accesscode, Apollousa, Underworld Goddess, Dweller, Bagooska, Baronne, Chengying, Elf; people are doing Stardust Dragon lines because they can. I know Tearlaments ARE the format, but I would still give zombies a try because they have never been so powerful.

With all that said, this is my deck! It could be 60 cards, and it could play more handtraps and it could even play branded. That is the point of zombies: pure creative liberty. My deck is built to mill; I can get through a turn and end with 6 cards in main and 4 in Extra. I don't play handtraps because I like to see how far I can take a deck with it's own power, and that means going first and praying they don't have hand traps, which in tear format means I have to watch out for an Imperm and a DD Crow which is more than doable.

I do not have enough monster zones, I often have to decide what would be the best end board I can make with only six monsters on it. Thanks to Elf, mezuki, and this decks amazing ability to spam lvl 8 monsters, Mad Mauler is the MVP. Make a lvl 10 synchro, bring back Chaos Ruler from the graveyard, bring back Mauler using elf, make another lvl 10 synchro, target one of those synchros with Mauler and summon Red-Eyes, to resummon that lvl 10 in the GY on your opponents turn. End Boards look like, Elf, Red-Eyes, Baronne, Chengying, Doomking, and Rulkallos. Sometimes I will hold off on the Red-Eyes effect to see what would be better, a Chengying, a Sycthe lock, or a second Doomking depending on how they respond to the first one. Sometimes you even have Superpoly or can send your Tears back with a shuffler only to mill again with Merrli and summon Dragostepelia. Anything, anything, anything you want do you can do with this deck, so start labbing because it has never been a better time to mill with zombies!

Hello I am back with another Mannadium deck profile post June 2023 banlist. The list has kinda changed since last time I posted the first draft but with some changes in the extra deck and and some changes to non-engine cards as well as the side deck. I took out droll and gamma for ash and bystials as well as I put D barrier in the side because they limited gamma, banned super heavy scarecrow, limited purely delicous. You can play droll if you want still if you feel you need it but I believe thats up to you for decide. I chose ash, bystials and D barrier because I am asumming more people will play Branded and Striker since Engane got semi limited and Multi role became unlimited. Ash hits Branded fusion of course and bystials hit the archetype in general which is why I added them in as well as Labrynth. Dimensional barrier is reall good agaisnt Branded and even Kash shutting them off of XYZ, though Kashtira will probably still be the best deck. However I have thought about playing Belle in either the main or side because in testing I rn into alot of bytsials that would banish Visas in GY which hurts alot sincehe is the heart and soul of the deck. I believe we are in a bystial format so be aware of that going forward so be prepared. Another card I thought about playing was destrudo which is another card to add off of Magnamut but I will test more with it and come back with an updated deck if it works. In the extra deck I added IP Masquerena and Underworld goddess. I found myslef having a hard time outing chaos angel going first so that is why I put Underworld goddess and IP was added as just a more easy way to make unicorn if needed. You can play Accesscode if you want which isnt a bad idea but I would need to test more with it and see if it works well.

deck_excerpt: Competitively viable Pure Sacred Beasts deck with synergistic consistency boosters.
deck_description:
INTRO

Greetings! First off, this is by no means a comprehensive guide as I can't get through everything here, so feel free to leave a comment below if you have any questions. I hope you will find this guide useful. If you're looking to learn more about this archetype, see the link below.

STRATEGY

This strategy revolves around summoning your Sacred Beasts (SB) by using the effects of Dark Summoning Beast (DSB) and Chaos Summoning Beast (CSB). You mainly want to use CSB for this, unless you don't care about not being able to attack on the turn you used DSB. To ensure consistency, we have cards like Dark Beckoning Beast (DBB) and Opening of the Spirit Gates (OSG), which I'll be reffering to as »searchers« in this guide. It's important to note, that we don't have any »one card combos« and need to draw our core pieces. This is why we play Piri Reis Map and Allure of Darkness, both excellent cards with their own purpose, but they also have synergy on their own, as Piri can generate fodder for Allure.

Ideally, you will be able to control either (or both) Hamon, Lord of Striking Thunder or Raviel, Lord of Phantasms along side Fallen Paradise to protect them and allowing you to draw 2 cards each turn. Having both of them on the field in addition to Awakening of the Sacred Beasts (ASB) is your ultimate goal. This is because ASB has a Skill Drain-like effect, which has amazing stun potential along side Cerulean Skyfire, which allows us to negate a Spell/Trap activation once per turn.

The Extra Deck doesn't really server any specific purpose, but fills the gaps in our Main Deck strategy instead. You might not always be able to or even want to use the ED. The Knightmare cards are important, because they offer us forms of removal. Salamangreat Almiraj is an essential part of the deck, however, as it can Link off any leftover searchers on the field. Same idea applies to Linkuriboh. Barricadeborg Blocker offers a form of protection and recursion for cards like Cerulean Skyfire, Fallen Paradise and Opening of the Spirit Gates (among other cards). Both Dharc the Dark Charmer, Gloomy and Aussa the Earth Charmer, Immovable are great form of extending plays and disrupting your opponents GY. I:P Masquerena is a great going first tool, if you're going to be able to trigger her effect and SS Apollousa, Bow of the Goddess on the enemy turn, allowing you to suddenly have free negates on your field. There are other generic ED monsters worth considering, but I feel like this is a good start to any pure Sacred Beast build.

OTHER CARDS & UPGRADES

You could always opt-in to run a variety of engines, but I'm not going to go over those options in this section. You can check the Discord link below, if you want to learn more about engines that synergize with Sacred Beasts. However, there are a couple option worth discussing here.

The side deck is pretty self explenatory. You need to run some form of Spell/Trap removal such as Cosmic Cyclone or Mystical Space Typhoon, as it's not always worth making Knightmares to deal with that. Raigeki can go hard, aspecially with Dark Ruler No More activated and I prefer this option to Lightning Storm, as you should always have cards on your field. Solemn Strike is optional, but it's great for going first. Radian, the Multidimensional Kaiju can be replaced with other "better" Kaijus, but his DARK typing synergizes with Allure of Darkness. Nibiru, the Primal Being can be swapped out, it's not always great, it depends entirely on your local scene (consider other options listen below).

When considering handtraps and other generic/staple cards, keep these options in your mind:Chaos Hunter, Crossout Designator, Droll & Lock Bird Effect Veiler (replace with Infinite Impermanence and add One for One if you prefer), Ghost Belle & Haunted Mansion, Ghost Ogre & Snow Rabbit and Appointer of the Red Lotus among other cards.

If you feel like spending more, consider adding cards like Forbidden Droplet, Triple Tactics Talent, Pot of Prosperity (replaces Allure, but it conflicts with Fallen Paradise draw effect) and Accesscode Talker among other cards.

THANK YOU

If you enjoyed this guide, please leave a comment and/or a reaction below. I post builds for less popular casual and non-meta builds semi-regularly, so feel free to follow me if you're interested in that sort of thing.

To learn more about this archetype, join the Sacred Beast Discord community: https://discord.gg/rYaeTZJAxr

Tricky Fairies, Skye Zaizen's deck. Trying to bring the best out of her character deck whilst keeping it in the VRAINS era. I'm not that knowledgeable on VRAINS so my apologies if anything seems off.

Let me know if you've got any ideas to improve it.

Guide
Any "Rokket" --> Striker Dragon --> Summon 2nd "Rokket" (either through Boot Sector Launch or another method) --> Striker & new monster for Dillingerous Dragon --> Summon Guardragon Pisty underneath --> Link 3/4/5 (Don't use Pisty for this) --> Activate Pisty's effect, summon "Rokket" --> Activate Dillingerous on the "Rokket" summon --> Link 4/5

Tips
Sending Absorouter Dragon to GY is a good idea, either use it to get Rokket Synchron, Rokket Tracer or Silverrokket Dragon (Rokket Caliber would also work but I don't have one). If Abso has already been used or they're all in the GY, Galactic Spiral Dragon is a good option.
- Tracer can be used to destroy Boot Sector for combo extentions
- Galactic Spiral Dragon, Noctovision Dragon, Red-Eyes Darkness Metal Dragon, White Dragon Wyverburster and Black Dragon Collapserpent are in here for combo extentions.
    - Probably would switch these cards when using side deck
- Moon Mirror Shield is here because it can be (I just like the card)

deck_name: Barrel Dragon Coin Flip Luck Deck
deck_excerpt: Bandit Keith's Barrel Dragon has gotten an upgrade!!
deck_description:
This is not one of my best decks, but a fun one nevertheless. Using no meta cards, this deck relies entirely on the luck of a coin flip! If you call right, pop a card! If you call wrong, well, lets talk about that later!

Use the monstrous, mechanical dragons known as Desperado Barrel Dragon, Barrel Dragon and Blowback Dragon to blast your opponents cards off the board, but remember, you must believe in your coin to get you the best hits! Even if you do get a tripe Tails, you can use Proton Blast in the GY to make all your results Heads. It's not cheating if it's written on the card!

Other than the Barrel Dragons, you also have Arcana Force EX - The Dark Ruler, who will be a 4000 ATK beatstick once you get three monsters on the field, flip a coin and see what upgrade you can get on him! Alongside Arcana, you also have JINZO The Machine Menace, alongside his trusty sidekick Returner. Jinzo The Machine Menance will special summon himself as a 2400 ATK monster while a trap is in the GY or face up on the field (not a Quick Effect). He can whenever tribute himself to rid all traps on the field and summon Returner, who when destroyed will summon Machine Menace again from the GY, but only for a turn, so use him wisely!

You also have cards like BM-4 Spider who can destroy an opponents monster and inflict burn damage, along with the old Blast Sphere that can do similar work. The mini Twin-Barrel Dragon can pop a card if it tosses two Heads. Keeper and Prisma help to get your Gatling Dragon on the field, Keeper can also summon a Barrel Dragon or Blowback from the Deck, but only in facedown defence position, flip him back up the next turn to activate his effect! Fusion Deployment is a free Barrel or Blowback Dragon from the Deck. Heavy Metal Raiders will upgrade your Barrel Dragons considerably, protecting them and boosting their ATK, while also summoning more Dark Machines! Limiter Removal will double your Barrel Dragons up to 5600 ATK (not permanent). 

Mirror Force is a classic way of protecting your board, and Call of The Haunted is yet another classic that brings back anything from the GY!

This isn't a great deck, but it is fun and nostalgic. Good luck!

Little Q&A

Q: why is crossout there?

A: it protects you from hand traps, also, if your oppenent doesn't hand trap you, just set it and pass when they try to evenly match you make there card fizzle away! (That's the reason you run 1 veiler, 1 ogre, and 1 evenly matched)

Q: No Iblee in main deck?

A: iblee is a very easy card to out, even if your oppenent doesn't have a link 1 they'll just normal summon a monster then go into phoneix (because everyone and there grandmas running it). But, I do believe it is worthy to side if your going up against lots of decks that don't want to give up there normal summon (purrely sometimes), can't normal summon (kashtira most of the time atleast), or decks that just don't want to special summon (floowandereeze). I would compare this card to ra's disciple in branded (which nobody runs emphasizing my point)
